## Cloudflare Origin Certificate Secret
##
## How to generate:
## 1. Go to Cloudflare Dashboard → qeylo.com → SSL/TLS → Origin Server
## 2. Click "Create Certificate"
## 3. Select: RSA (2048), hostnames: *.qeylo.com, qeylo.com
## 4. Validity: 15 years
## 5. Copy the Origin Certificate → paste as tls.crt below
## 6. Copy the Private Key → paste as tls.key below
##
## Then create the secret on the cluster:
##   kubectl create secret tls cloudflare-origin-cert \
##     --cert=origin-cert.pem \
##     --key=origin-key.pem \
##     -n production
##
##   kubectl create secret tls cloudflare-origin-cert \
##     --cert=origin-cert.pem \
##     --key=origin-key.pem \
##     -n staging
##
## The wildcard cert (*.qeylo.com) covers both qeylo.com and staging.qeylo.com.
##
## IMPORTANT: Set Cloudflare SSL mode to "Full (Strict)" for this to work.
